parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the vehicle's frame can lead to structural failure, loss of steering control, and potentially cause accidents, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Unusual noises while driving
loss of steering control
corrosion on the exterior front fenders
rusted-out holes on the frame
detachment of the steering shaft
and failure of the strut towers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Strut Tower and Filler Tube Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the strut towers and filler tubes can cause the struts to fail, leading to loss of steering control and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the strut towers and filler tubes
failure of the struts
and loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank can cause fuel to overflow, leading to a fire hazard and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank does not indicate when it is at full capacity
fuel overflows
and rust failure on the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame and Body Strut Housing Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the frame and body strut housing can cause structural failure, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clicking sound while turning
rocking or wobbling of the vehicle
severe steering wheel vibration
loud noise while driving over bumps
and rust or corrosion visible on the frame and strut housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Corrosion and Steering Column Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame and strut tower housing can cause the power steering column to fracture, leading to a loss of steering control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Knocking noise in the front of the vehicle
wheel shaking while turning
vehicle swaying uncontrollably while turning
power steering failure
steering wheel becomes extremely hard to maneuver
steering wheel seizes without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the gauges and lighting on the instrument panel can distract the driver, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The gauges and lighting on the instrument panel fail to function or malfunction while driving
especially at speeds above 30 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Battery, Starter, and Ignition)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded or causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle requires frequent jump-starting
the battery needs to be replaced multiple times
the starter fails
the ignition system malfunctions
and the vehicle fails to crank or start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Electrical System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes and electrical system can cause accidents or loss of control, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to function properly
making it difficult to stop the vehicle
and the tail lights are inoperable
reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Issues (Dealership Failure to Assist)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to assist with recall repairs can lead to prolonged exposure to safety risks and inconvenience to vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships refuse to perform recall repairs
fail to provide assistance
or do not follow through on promises to repair vehicles.
